sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M31511
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: HpaI to BamHI section of M13K07 genome - refactor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a refactored genome for the M13K07 bacteriophage. We are only focusing on the part of the genome from the HpaI site to the BamHI site. We will attempt to separate all genes in this range so that there are no overlapping regions so that we may later manipulate them individually.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Lee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is a modified version of the M13K07 genome (Part BBa_M1307).
